  Qed.

  Lemma propagation_init' [MN0 : MNet] [n n' m] [v ] [DS] :
    KIC MN0 →
    dead_set DS '' MN0 →
    In n DS →
    lock MN0 n n' →
    List.In (MqRecv (m, Q) v) (mserv_q (MN0 n)) →
    ∃ MN1 mpath,
      (MN0 =[mpath]=> MN1)
      ∧ detect_path DS mpath
      ∧ sends_probe (m, R) (active_probe_of MN1 n) (NetMod.get n MN1).

  Proof.
    intros.
    assert (well_formed '' MN0) by eauto with LTS.

    assert (∃ mpath0 MN1 MQ1 s S1,
               (MN0 =[mpath0]=> MN1)
               ∧ detect_path DS mpath0
               ∧ NetMod.get n MN1 = mserv (MqRecv (m, Q) v :: MQ1) ((MRecv s)) S1
           ) as Hxx'.
    {
      specialize (flush_one_In ltac:(eauto)) as ?.
      hsimpl in ×.
      ∃ mpath, MN1, (MQ01 ++ MQ1'), s, S1.
      repeat split > [attac | | attac].
      apply detect_path_incl with (DS0:=[n]).
      ieattac.
      eattac.
    }
    hsimpl in Hxx'.

    assert (∃ mpath1 MN2 M2 S2,
               (MN1 =[mpath1]=> MN2)
               ∧ detect_path DS mpath1
               ∧ NetMod.get n MN2 = mserv MQ1 (MSend (m, R) (active_probe_of MN2 n) M2) S2
           ) as Hx.
    {

      destruct S1 as [I1 P1 O1].
      pose (serv (I1 ++ [(m, Q, v)]) P1 O1) as S2.
      pose {|self := self s
            ; lock_count := lock_count s
            ; locked := locked s
            ; wait := m :: wait s
            ; alarm := alarm s
            |} as s1.
      pose (NetMod.put n (mserv MQ1 (mon_handle (MqRecv (m, Q) v) s ) S2) MN1) as MN1'.

      ∃ [NTau n (MActP (Recv (m, Q) v))], MN1', (MRecv s1), S2.

      destruct s.
      subst MN1' s1 S2.

      assert (locked0 ≠ None).
      {
        consider (KIC MN1) by eauto with LTS.
        consider (∃ path, '' MN0 =[path]=> '' MN1) by eauto using transp_sound with LTS.
        assert (dead_set DS '' MN1) by eauto with LTS.
        assert (deadlocked n '' MN0) by (∃ DS; eauto with LTS).
        assert (lock MN1 n n') by eauto with LTS.
        specialize (H_lock_C n n' ltac:(auto)).
        ltac1:(autounfold with LTS_get in H_lock_C).
        rewrite `(NetMod.get n MN1 = _) in H_lock_C.
        simpl in ×.
        bs.
      }
      assert (n = self0).
      {
        consider (KIC MN1) by eauto with LTS.
        specialize (H_self_C n).
        ltac1:(autounfold with LTS_get in H_self_C).
        rewrite `(NetMod.get n MN1 = _) in H_self_C.
        auto.
      }

      destruct locked0. 2: bs.
      subst.

      repeat split > [attac | | attac].
      - hsimpl in |- ×.
        eapply path_seq0.
        constructor. constructor.
        constructor. hrewrite NetMod.get.
        attac.
      - eapply detect_path_incl with (DS0:=[self0]). ieattac.
        eapply detect_path1. constructor; attac.
      - unfold active_probe_of, NetGet.
        hsimpl in ×.
        attac.
    }
    hsimpl in Hx.

    ∃ MN2, (mpath0 ++ mpath1).
    repeat split > [eattac | | eattac].
    - eapply detect_path_app; auto.
    - rewrite `(NetMod.get n MN2 = _).
      constructor.
  Qed.

  Lemma propagation_init_finito [MN0 : MNet] [n m] [v] DS :
    KIC MN0 →
    dead_set DS MN0 →
    trans_lock MN0 n m →
    In n DS →
    List.In (MqRecv (m, Q) v) (mserv_q (MN0 n)) →
    ∃ MN1 mpath,
      (MN0 =[mpath]=> MN1)
      ∧ detect_path DS mpath
      ∧ (∃ n', trans_lock MN0 n n' ∧ alarm (MN1 n') = true).

  Proof.
    intros.
    assert (well_formed '' MN0) by eauto with LTS.

    assert (lock MN0 m n) by eauto using mserv_Q_lock_sound.
    assert (trans_lock MN0 n n) by eauto with LTS.
    assert (deadlocked n '' MN0) by (∃ DS; eauto 2 with LTS).

    consider (∃ MN1 mpath0,
                 (MN0 =[mpath0]=> MN1)
                 ∧ detect_path DS mpath0
                 ∧ sends_probe (m, R) (active_probe_of MN1 n) (NetMod.get n MN1))
      by (consider (trans_lock MN0 n n) by eauto using propagation_init'; eauto using propagation_init').

    consider (∃ ppath, '' MN0 =[ppath]=> '' MN1) by eauto using transp_sound.
    have (well_formed '' MN1) by eauto with LTS.
    have (KIC MN1) by auto with LTS.

    assert (deadlocked n '' MN1) by auto with LTS.
    assert (lock MN1 m n) by eauto with LTS.
    assert (trans_lock MN1 n n) by eauto with LTS.
    assert (trans_lock MN1 n m) by eauto with LTS.

    consider (∃ mpath1 MN2, (MN1 =[mpath1]=> MN2) ∧ _ ∧ alarm (MN2 n) = true)
      by eauto using propagation_finito, active_active_probe_of with LTS.

    ∃ MN2, (mpath0 ++ mpath1).
    eattac.
  Qed.

  Lemma locked_serv_deinstr :
    ∀ (MN0 MN1 : MNet) a n,
      SRPC_net MN0 →
      deadlocked n MN0 →
      Flushing_NAct n a →
      (MN0 =(a)=> MN1) →
      deinstr MN0 = deinstr MN1.

  Proof.
    intros.

    consider (∃ n', lock MN0 n n')
      by (eapply deadlocked_M_get_lock; eattac).

    destruct a; consider (Flushing_NAct _ _).
    - destruct m; doubt.
      + destruct p; doubt.
        unfold deinstr in ×.
        apply NetMod.extensionality.
        intros.
        repeat (rewrite NetMod.get_map in × ).
        consider (_ =(_)=> _).
        hsimpl in ×.
        smash_eq n n1; attac.
        unfold serv_deinstr.
        attac.
        compat_hsimpl in *; attac.
        repeat (rewrite <- app_assoc). attac.
      + destruct p; doubt.
      + destruct a; doubt.
        unfold deinstr in ×.
        apply NetMod.extensionality.
        intros.
        repeat (rewrite NetMod.get_map in × ).
        consider (_ =(_)=> _).
        hsimpl in ×.
        smash_eq n n0; attac.
        unfold serv_deinstr.
        attac.
    - apply deinstr_act in H2.
      hsimpl in ×.
      destruct p; doubt; attac.
      enough (n ≠ n) by bs.
      eapply lock_no_send; eauto.
  Qed.

  Lemma locked_serv_deinstrs :
    ∀ MN0 MN1 mpath DS,
      well_formed '' MN0 →
      dead_set DS '' MN0 →
      Forall (fun a ⇒ ∃ n, In n DS ∧ Flushing_NAct n a) mpath →
      (MN0 =[mpath]=> MN1) →
      deinstr MN0 = deinstr MN1.

  Proof.
    intros.
    generalize dependent MN0.
    induction mpath; attac.
    rename N1 into MN0'.
    transitivity '(deinstr MN0').
    - eapply locked_serv_deinstr; eauto with LTS.
      ∃ DS; eattac.
    - apply deinstr_act in H2.
      destruct (MNAct_to_PNAct a); eattac.
      hrewrite ('' MN0) in ×.
      eapply IHmpath; eauto with LTS.
  Qed.

  Lemma locked_flushed :
    ∀ MN0 MN1 a n,
      SRPC_net '' MN0 →
      deadlocked n '' MN0 →
      Flushing_NAct n a →
      (MN0 =(a)=> MN1) →
      flushed MN0 →
      flushed MN1.

  Proof.
    intros.

    unfold flushed, flushed_in, Flushed in ×.
    intros.
    specialize (H3 n) as Hx.
    specialize (H3 n0) as Hx0.
    destruct (NetMod.get n0 MN0) as [MQ0 M0 S0] eqn:?.
    destruct (NetMod.get n0 MN1) as [MQ1 M1 S1] eqn:?.
    destruct a; kill H1.
    + smash_eq n0 n.
        × consider (_ =(_)=> _); hsimpl in ×.
          destruct m; attac.
          -- destruct p; doubt.
             unfold deinstr, serv_deinstr, ready_in, ready, apply_instr, instr_for, NetGet in ×.
             compat_hsimpl in *; attac.
          -- destruct a; doubt.
             unfold deinstr, serv_deinstr, ready_in, ready, apply_instr, instr_for, NetGet in ×.
             compat_hsimpl in *; attac.
        × assert (NetMod.get n0 MN0 = NetMod.get n0 MN1) by eattac.
          unfold ready_in, ready, apply_instr, instr_for, NetGet in ×.
          attac.
      + smash_eq n0 n.
        × consider (_ =(_)=> _); hsimpl in ×.
          unfold deinstr, serv_deinstr, ready_in, ready, apply_instr, instr_for, NetGet in ×.
          destruct p; compat_hsimpl in *; doubt.
          smash_eq n0 n2; blast_cases; attac.
        × smash_eq n0 n2.
          -- consider (_ =(_)=> _).
             assert (NetMod.get n0 MN0 = NetMod.get n0 N0') by eauto using eq_sym, NV_stay.
             hsimpl in ×.
             unfold ready_in, ready, apply_instr, instr_for, NetGet in ×.
             rewrite <- `(NetMod.get n0 _ = _) in ×.
             hsimpl in ×.
             hsimpl in ×.
             blast_cases; attac.
          -- assert (NetMod.get n0 MN0 = NetMod.get n0 MN1) by eattac.
             unfold ready_in, ready, apply_instr, instr_for, NetGet in ×.
             attac.
  Qed.

  Lemma locked_flusheds :
    ∀ MN0 MN1 mpath DS,
      well_formed '' MN0 →
      dead_set DS '' MN0 →
      Forall (fun a ⇒ ∃ n, In n DS ∧ Flushing_NAct n a) mpath →
      (MN0 =[mpath]=> MN1) →
      flushed MN0 →
      flushed MN1.

  Proof.
    intros.
    generalize dependent MN0.
    induction mpath; attac.
    assert (flushed N1); eauto using locked_flushed with LTS.
    - eapply locked_flushed; eauto with LTS.
      ∃ DS; eattac.
    - apply deinstr_act in H2.
      destruct (MNAct_to_PNAct a); eattac.
      hrewrite ('' MN0) in ×.
      eapply IHmpath; eauto with LTS.
  Qed.

  Lemma to_instr : ∀ chans MN0,
      (∀ n, not (In n chans) → ready_in n MN0) →
      flushed MN0 →
      ∃ mnpath i1,
        (MN0 =[mnpath]=> apply_instr i1 MN0).

  Proof.
    intros.
    destruct (@flushed_ready chans MN0 ltac:(auto) ltac:(auto)) as (mpath & MN1 & ?).
    hsimpl in ×.
    destruct (@flushed_ready_instr MN1 ltac:(auto) ltac:(auto)) as [i ?].
    ∃ mpath, i.
    hrewrite ('' MN0).
    rewrite <- `(MN1 = _).
    auto.
  Qed.

  Lemma KIC_AnySRPC_serv_instr [I : instr] [N] : KIC (I N) →
                                               ∀ n, AnySRPC_serv (NetMod.get n N).
  Proof.
    intros ?.
    consider (KIC _); attac.
  Qed.

  #[export] Hint Immediate KIC_AnySRPC_serv_instr : LTS.

  Lemma net_preserve_alarm_path
    : ∀ mpath (MN0 MN1 : MNet) (n : Transp.Net.NAME.t'),
      KIC MN0 → MN0 =[ mpath ]=> MN1 → alarm (MN0 n) = true → alarm (MN1 n) = true.

  Proof.
    induction mpath; attac.
    eapply IHmpath with (MN0:=N1); eauto 3 using net_preserve_alarm with LTS.
  Qed.

  Lemma KIC_instr_well_formed : ∀ (i : instr) N, KIC (i N) → well_formed N.
  Proof.
    intros.
    consider (KIC _); hsimpl in *; auto.
  Qed.
  #[export] Hint Immediate KIC_instr_well_formed : LTS.

  Lemma ac_to_alarm [MN0 : MNet] [n] :
    KIC MN0 →
    alarm_condition n MN0 →
    trans_lock MN0 n n →
    ∃ DS mpath MN1, (MN0 =[mpath]=> MN1) ∧ dead_set DS MN0 ∧ detect_path DS mpath ∧ alarm (MN1 n) = true.

  Proof.
    intros.

    assert (deadlocked n '' MN0) as [DS [? ?]] by eauto using dep_self_deadlocked with LTS.

    ∃ DS.

    destruct (alarm (MN0 n)) eqn:?.
    1: { ∃ [], MN0. unfold detect_path; eattac. }

    consider (alarm_condition n MN0).
    - consider (n = m ∨ trans_lock MN0 n m).
      + consider (∃ mpath MN1, (MN0 =[ mpath ]=> MN1) ∧ detect_path DS mpath ∧ alarm (MN1 m) = true)
          by eauto using propagation_finito, active_active_probe_of with LTS.
        ∃ mpath, MN1. split; eauto with LTS.
      + consider (∃ mpath MN1, (MN0 =[ mpath ]=> MN1) ∧ detect_path DS mpath ∧ alarm (MN1 n) = true)
          by eauto using propagation_finito, active_active_probe_of with LTS.
        ∃ mpath, MN1. split; eauto with LTS.

    - assert (deadlocked n '' MN0) by (∃ DS; eauto).
      consider (∃ MN1 mpath, (MN0 =[mpath]=> MN1) ∧ detect_path [n] mpath ∧ alarm (MN1 n) = true)
        by eauto using detection_finito with LTS.
      ∃ mpath, MN1.
      repeat (split; eauto).
      eapply detect_path_incl; eauto.
      ieattac.
  Qed.

  Lemma ac_to_alarm_instr [MN0 : MNet] [n] :
    KIC MN0 →
    alarm_condition n MN0 →
    trans_lock MN0 n n →
    flushed MN0 →
    ready_net MN0 →
    ∃ mpath (i0 : instr), (MN0 =[mpath]=> i0 MN0) ∧ alarm (i0 MN0 n) = true.

  Proof.
    intros.

    consider (∃ DS mpath0 MN1,
                 (MN0 =[ mpath0 ]=> MN1)
                 ∧ dead_set DS MN0
                 ∧ detect_path DS mpath0
                 ∧ alarm (MN1 n) = true
             ) by eauto using ac_to_alarm with LTS.

    consider (∃ mpath1 (i1 : instr), (MN1 =[mpath1]=> i1 MN1)).
    {
      assert (flushed MN1).
      {
        assert (flushed MN0) by eauto using apply_instr_flushed.
        assert (well_formed '' MN0) by eauto 10 with LTS.
        eauto using locked_flusheds.
      }
      assert (∀ n'', not (In n'' (path_particip mpath0)) → ready_in n'' MN1).
      {
        intros.
        assert (ready_in n'' MN0) by eauto.
        unfold ready_in in ×.
        replace (NetMod.get n'' MN1) with (NetMod.get n'' MN0) by eauto using path_particip_stay.
        blast_cases.
        eauto using apply_instr_ready.
      }
      eauto using to_instr.
    }

    replace (deinstr MN0) with (deinstr MN1)
      by (symmetry; eapply locked_serv_deinstrs; eauto with LTS).

    ∃ (mpath0 ++ mpath1), i1.

    assert (KIC MN1) by eauto with LTS.
    eauto using net_preserve_alarm_path, dead_set_dep_in with LTS.
  Qed.

  Theorem KIC_detection_complete : ∀ (i0 : instr) N0 MN1 mpath0 DS,
      KIC (i0 N0) →
      (i0 N0 =[ mpath0 ]=> MN1) →
      dead_set DS MN1 →
      ∃ mpath1 MN2 n, (MN1 =[ mpath1 ]=> MN2) ∧ In n DS ∧ alarm (MN2 n) = true.

  Proof.
    intros.
    assert (KIC MN1) by eauto with LTS.
    consider (∃ n, In n DS ∧ trans_lock MN1 n n) by (eauto 8 using dead_set_cycle with LTS).
    consider (∃ n', trans_lock MN1 n n' ∧ alarm_condition n' MN1) by (consider (KIC MN1); attac).
    assert (trans_lock MN1 n' n') by (eauto using dep_reloop with LTS).
    consider (∃ DS mpath1 MN2, (MN1 =[ mpath1 ]=> MN2) ∧ dead_set DS MN1 ∧ _ ∧ alarm (MN2 n') = true)
      by eauto using ac_to_alarm with LTS.

    ∃ mpath1, MN2, n'.
    now eauto with LTS.
  Qed.

  Check KIC_detection_complete.

  Corollary find_detection : ∀ (i0 : instr) (N0 N1 : Net) path (DS : Names),
      KIC (i0 N0) →
      (N0 =[ path ]=> N1) →
      dead_set DS N1 →
      ∃ mpath (i1 : instr) n,
        (i0 N0 =[ mpath ]=> i1 N1)
        ∧ In n DS
        ∧ alarm (i1 N1 n) = true.

  Proof.
    intros.
    consider (∃ mpath0 (i1 : instr), i0 N0 =[ mpath0 ]=> i1 N1)
      by eauto using transp_complete.
    consider (∃ n, In n DS ∧ trans_lock N1 n n)
      by (eapply dead_set_cycle; eauto with LTS).
    consider (∃ n', trans_lock (i1 N1) n n' ∧ alarm_condition n' (i1 N1))
      by (consider (KIC (i1 N1)); attac).
    assert (trans_lock (i1 N1) n' n')
      by (hsimpl; eauto using dep_reloop with LTS).

    consider (∃ mpath1 (i2 : instr), (i1 N1 =[ mpath1 ]=> i2 _) ∧ alarm (i2 _ n') = true)
      by eauto using ac_to_alarm_instr, apply_instr_flushed, apply_instr_ready_net with LTS.

    ∃ (mpath0 ++ mpath1), i2, n'.
    now eauto using net_preserve_alarm_path with LTS.
  Qed.
End COMPL_F.
